Today is the 150th anniversary of the surrender of Confederate Gen . 
  Robert E . 
  Lee to Union Lt . 
  Gen . 
  Ulysses S . 
  Grant in Appomattox, Virginia . 
  Thursday's commemoration included a re-enactment of Lee's last clash with Grant's troops and of the Confederate surrender in a Virginia farmhouse on April 9, 1865 . 
  Lee's surrender marked the beginning of the end of the Civil War in 1865 . 
 